The paper discusses Secure Multi-Party Computation (SMC) and its various applications, which are typically covered under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), cybersecurity (cs.CY), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on a modified version of the ck-Secure Sum protocol, which is a cryptographic protocol used in SMC, indicating a higher likelihood of the paper belonging to the cs.CR category. However, the paper also discusses the use of secure sum computation in privacy-preserving distributed data mining, which suggests a possible fit for the cs.DB category. The other categories are also relevant to the subject matter of the paper, but to a lesser extent.
